item.title: [First wepon Model] The Sword of Ownagness [First wepon Model]
item.dc:creator: @shrogg shrogg
item.description:
@shrogg wrote:

OK, i see you have followed my instruction’s perfectly, now that it’s 3D, you can sharpen it and make the handle round

[ul][li]seclect “rect”[/li]
[li]now click and drag over the aera that you want sharpend[/li]
[li]press “q” and the “scale” tool should appear.[/li]
[li]looking at the pictures you have supplyed, drag the “green” box down[/li]
[li]the section you seclected should shrink inward’s[/li]
[li]repeat over the aera’s you want sharpend[/li]
[li]now you can do the same in the aera’s that you want rounded, but this time not drag the green box down as far.[/li][/ul]

i hope i have helped

Cheer’s ~ Shrogg

item.title: [First wepon Model] The Sword of Ownagness [First wepon Model]
item.dc:creator: @shrogg shrogg
item.description:
@shrogg wrote:

here’s how to make it 3d =P

you might not get what i mean, but oh well

•press “control + C”
•control + V
•press “V” (thats the keybord shortcut to move)
•use the green arrow to pull your copy down
•press the “create” button
•make sure the “create” tool is set to “face”
•fill up the gaps that the copying made
•“mat” your model

Or use primitive’s they are Sooooo mutch easyer
